        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 2:54PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 254 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Lake Somerville State Park &amp; Trailway, or 8 miles
southeast of Caldwell, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caldwell, Somerville, Snook, Lake Somerville State Park &amp; Trailway,
and Lyons.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
